{
    // Always use the container preset
   // "cmake.configureOnOpen": false,
    "cmake.preferredGenerators": ["Ninja"],
  //  "cmake.configurePreset": "Debug",
   // "cmake.buildPreset": "Debug",

    // Use container tools (do NOT override with host paths)
    "cmake.cmakePath": "cmake",

    // Cppcheck inside container
    "cppcheck.enable": true,
    "cppcheck.cppcheckPath": "cppcheck",

    // Include paths inside your repo (mounted into container)
    "cppcheck.includePaths": [
       //  "${workspaceFolder}/Core/Inc",
      //   "${workspaceFolder}/Drivers/CMSIS/Include",
       //  "${workspaceFolder}/Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS"
    ],

    // MISRA + C11
    "cppcheck.standards": ["c11"],
    "cppcheck.platform": "unix32",
    "cppcheck.misraAdddon": true,

    // Better IntelliSense for ARM embedded
    "C_Cpp.default.configurationProvider": "ms-vscode.cmake-tools"
}



/**
  * @brief  The application entry point.


{
    "cmake.cmakePath": "/opt/homebrew/bin/cmake",
    "cmake.configureArgs": [],
    "cmake.preferredGenerators": [
        "Ninja"
    ]
}


What happens:

✅ Cppcheck runs with explicit path (guaranteed to find it)
✅ MISRA 2012 checks enabled
✅ Knows where your include files are (catches header errors)
✅ Correct platform detection (32-bit vs 64-bit)
✅ C11 standard enforced
✅ More likely to catch real issues




  * @retval int
  */